    {
      "id": "5a93c517_79c70b65",
      "file_path": "appc-config/appc-config-adaptor/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/appc/ccadaptor/ConfigComponentAdaptor.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 964,
      "message": "Oh, I see.  The original code captured everything, including the XML tags, \"<configuration>xxx</configuration>\".  With the changes, if the input were \"<configuration><data>xxx</data></configuration>\" then it will now capture just \"<configuration>xxx\".  So now it will only include the leading \"configuration\" tag, it will leave out both the leading and trailing \"data\" tags, AND it will leave out the trailing \"configuration\" tag.  Is this really what it should do?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-27 19:45:12.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_d18cf9d9",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_3988a321",
      "file_path": "appc-config/appc-config-adaptor/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/appc/ccadaptor/ConfigComponentAdaptor.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 964,
      "message": "Seems to me that the expectation is that the data tag is outside the configuration tag and the entire text within the configuration tags is extracted. The unit test case added justifies the same as well. <data><configuration>XXX</configuration></data> and the entire text between the data tags is extracted.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1989,
        "name": "Ramya Balaji",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "rb111y@att.com",
        "username": "rb111y"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-27 20:07:34.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_79c70b65",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_39b663dd",
      "file_path": "appc-config/appc-config-adaptor/provider/src/main/java/org/onap/appc/ccadaptor/ConfigComponentAdaptor.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 964,
      "message": "In that case, I'm confused as to why this was changed at all, since it already captured everything including the \"configuration\" tags.  The changes lead me to believe that it's trying to capture stuff when the \"configuration\" element is missing.  Or maybe it's trying to capture other stuff that's inside of \"data\", but outside of \"configuration\".  If so, it only captures stuff up to and including \"configuration\"; it won't capture anything that appears after the \"configuration\" element.  So given \"<data><hello>world</hello><configuration>abc</configuration><after>bye</after></data>\", it will capture \"<hello>world</hello><configuration>abc</configuration>\" and will not capture \"<after>bye</after>\".",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-27 20:37:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_3988a321",
      "unresolved": false
    },
